 Sooliman said their intervention in Graaff Reinet was an extension of their major intervention in Eastern Cape area. 
 He said: "The entire town went crazy with joy, gratitude and appreciation. People were waving to us in the streets, everyone came out of the businesses to greet and hooters were blaring."

